{"abstract":[{"text":"Adds a message filter. Filters are handlers that are run on all","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"incoming and outgoing messages, prior to standard dispatch. Filters"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"are run in the order that they were added.  The same handler can be","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"added as a filter more than once, in which case it will be run more"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"than once.  Filters added during a filter callback won’t be run on"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the message being processed. Filter functions are allowed to modify"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"and even drop messages."}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DBusConnectionRef\/addFilter(filterFunction:userData:userDataFreeFunc:)"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"addFilter","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"filterFunction","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GDBusMessageFilterFunction","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"GDBusMessageFilterFunction"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"userData","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"gpointer","preciseIdentifier":"c:gtypes.h@T@gpointer","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"? = nil, "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"userDataFreeFunc"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"GDestroyNotify","preciseIdentifier":"c:gtypes.h@T@GDestroyNotify"},{"text":"?) -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Discussion","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that filters are run in a dedicated message handling thread so"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"they can’t block and, generally, can’t do anything but signal a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"worker thread. Also note that filters are rarely needed - use API"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"such as ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_dbus_connection_send_message_with_reply()"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_dbus_connection_signal_subscribe()"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_dbus_connection_call()"},{"type":"text","text":" instead."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If a filter consumes an incoming message the message is not","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"dispatched anywhere else - not even the standard dispatch machinery","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(that API such as ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_dbus_connection_signal_subscribe()"},{"text":" and","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_dbus_connection_send_message_with_reply()"},{"type":"text","text":" relies on) will see the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"message. Similarly, if a filter consumes an outgoing message, the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"message will not be sent to the other peer.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"userDataFreeFunc"},{"type":"text","text":" is non-"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"text":", it will be called (in the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"thread-default main context of the thread you are calling this"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"method from) at some point after "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"userData"},{"type":"text","text":" is no longer"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"needed. (It is not guaranteed to be called synchronously when the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"filter is removed, and may be called after ","type":"text"},{"code":"connection","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" has been"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"destroyed.)"}]}]}],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"GIO"}],"extendedModule":"GIO","role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Instance Method","externalID":"s:3GIO22DBusConnectionProtocolPAAE9addFilter14filterFunction8userData0iJ8FreeFuncSiSpySo13_GDBusMessageVGSgSpySo01_mC0VGSg_AKs5Int32VSvSgtXC_ARyARXCSgtF::SYNTHESIZED::s:3GIO17DBusConnectionRefV","title":"addFilter(filterFunction:userData:userDataFreeFunc:)","symbolKind":"method","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"addFilter"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"filterFunction","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"GDBusMessageFilterFunction","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GDBusMessageFilterFunction"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"text":"userData","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:gtypes.h@T@gpointer","text":"gpointer"},{"kind":"text","text":"?, "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"userDataFreeFunc"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"GDestroyNotify","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:gtypes.h@T@GDestroyNotify"},{"kind":"text","text":"?) -> "},{"text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","kind":"typeIdentifier"}]},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DBusConnectionRef","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DBusConnectionRef\/DBusConnectionProtocol-Implementations"]]},"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/dbusconnectionref\/addfilter